answers.body_markdown:
I don&#39;t think `wp_prepare_attachment_for_js()` includes custom image sizes by default - you need to include them by means of the `image_size_names_choose` filter.

I had problems with this function recently, when the Advanced Custom Fields Pro plugin removed a filter override to `wp_prepare_attachment_for_js()` - this was making all image sizes available to the `wp_prepare_attachment_for_js()`, and was removed in ACF 5.8.3: https://github.com/AdvancedCustomFields/acf/commit/66b1383e5614188c20fc5ff8ae04bb9dc0e154f6#diff-e2ae20a151c20a3d2975705c600fae75L378. 

Try adding the following to add your additional image sizes:

    &lt;?php
    add_filter(&#39;image_size_names_choose&#39;, function($atts) {
        // Get an array of custom image sizes
    	$allImageSizes = wp_get_additional_image_sizes();
    	$imageSizes = [];

        // Loop through the custom images, make a suitable array
    	foreach ($allImageSizes as $key =&gt; $value) {
    		$imageSizes[$key] = $key;
    	}

        // Merge the new array with the existing, and return
    	$atts = array_merge($atts, $imageSizes);
    	return $atts;
    });

