You can create a copy of the items like this:

    var itemsCopy = assignmentPage.reprintItemListView.Items.Cast&lt;object&gt;().ToArray();

It is still not safe though to create this copy in a different thread than the UI thread. You may still get some rare *Collection was modified...* exceptions. To make it 100% safe you must create the copy while still running in the UI thread. To pass the copy in the `newAppsThread` you could use a [`ParameterizedThreadStart`][1]:

    var reprintAppsThread = new Thread(itemsCopy =&gt;

    //...

    reprintAppsThread.Start(
        assignmentPage.reprintItemListView.Items.Cast&lt;object&gt;().ToArray());


  [1]: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.threading.parameterizedthreadstart

